question.title: Dependency Resolution Issue after Upgrading Spring Boot Version
question.body:
I am in the process of upgrading our project from Spring Boot version 1.3.8 to Spring Boot version 2.7.15 to address known vulnerabilities.

As part of the upgrade, I am using Spring Framework version 5.3.41, which is required to resolve the issues.

However, while most of the dependencies are being resolved successfully from Maven Central (https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2), I am encountering an issue with the following dependency:

com.succsoft:spring-jcl:jar:5.3.41

The error I am receiving during the mvn clean install process is:

Could not resolve dependencies for project com.api:api-abstract-layer:war:1.0.0: Failure to find com.succsoft:spring-jcl:jar:5.3.41 in https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2 was cached in the local repository, resolution will not be reattempted until the update interval of central has elapsed or updates are forced

Could anyone please help me resolve this issue or suggest an alternative approach to address the dependency resolution for spring-jcl?
